        "Rain is heavy, sleep is deep, and an argument is strong: collocation is memory, not logic.",
        "You depend on a thing and are oblivious to it; the wrong preposition leaks the mother tongue.",
        "Where speech would ramble, good prose packs the action into a noun — the government's handling of the crisis.",
