        "A comma asks for a brief pause; a semicolon holds a longer one without closing the thought.",
        "The colon makes a promise: whatever follows will deliver what the clause has just announced.",
        "An em-dash breaks in — abruptly, theatrically — where a quieter writer would whisper inside parentheses.",
        "The humble en-dash spans a range, linking 1939–45 or the Oxford–Cambridge rivalry.",
        "English keeps no dash between a subject and its verb; 'London is the capital' needs the verb to be.",
